{{Quote|I don't recognize your face. You're new to the business. What's your name?''"<br />"''Never mind my name. Don't try to sweet-talk me, Fett. I heard you were dangerous. Heard you were the best. You don't seem that hot to me, Fett. We took you pretty easy. Pretty easy.|[[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] being held hostage by Furlag|<ref name="sote" />}}
'''Furlag''' was a small-time [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] with large, batlike ears. Operating during the height of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], he was not well-known, but often worked with other prominent bounty hunters, such as [[Zuckuss/Legends|Zuckuss]] and [[4-LOM/Legends|4-LOM]]. He, Zuckuss, and 4-LOM were subcontracted by fellow hunter [[Skorr/Legends|Skorr]] on [[Ord Mantell/Legends|Ord Mantell]] during the early [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] in the hunt for a group of prospective [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebels]]. The bounty hunters tracked them to a [[Spaceport/Legends|spaceport]] on Ord Mantell; they found Rebel agent [[Raleigh Dawn|Kestrel]] there, and began firing at her, but the Rebel was able to escape into a ship. Furlag's quarry was able to flee the [[Planet/Legends|planet]]. Furlag held Skorr responsible for the botching of the mission, and was furious with the other hunter.

[[3 ABY/Legends|Several years later]], Furlag again teamed up with 4-LOM and Zuckuss as well as several other bounty hunters including the [[Trandoshan/Legends|Trandoshan]] [[Bossk/Legends|Bossk]] to attempt to pry [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo's]] [[Carbonite/Legends|carbonite]]-encased body from [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]]. Furlag was present along with several other members of the loose coalition during an attempt on Fett's life on [[Gall/Legends|Gall]], which was intended to distract the [[Mandalorian/Legends|Mandalorian]] long enough for other bounty hunters to retrieve Solo from his ship, [[Slave I/Legends|''Slave I'']]. Fett escaped, though, and fled the planet; Furlag and the others gave chase in Bossk's ship, the [[Hound's Tooth/Legends|''Hound's Tooth'']], eventually catching up with Fett. Furlag was part of a boarding party which managed to apprehend and disarm Fett on ''Slave I''. The batlike bounty hunter was then charged with escorting Fett to the ship's [[force cage]]s and imprisoning him. Fett, however, was able to outsmart the less-experienced bounty hunter; in an elevator, he activated an unused crawl shaft, sending Furlag to meet his [[Death/Legends|death]] in [[Realspace/Legends|space]].

==Biography==
===Working for Skorr on Ord Mantell===
{{Quote|Grah! Heck of a party, Skorr&hellip;Too bad you ''forgot'' the favors!|Furlag, to Skorr, after Kestrel's escape|<ref name="rr">''[[Rookies: Rendezvous]]''</ref>}}
[[File:Furlag_sote.jpg|thumb|left|150px|Furlag confronts Boba Fett.]]

A tall [[Humanoid/Legends|humanoid]] [[Gender/Legends|male]] with large, batlike ears, a brown-furred body, and a set of sharp teeth, Furlag was a [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunter]] operating during the early years of the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]]. He wasn't well known, though, among his fellow bounty hunters, and he did not have much of a reputation.<ref name="sote" /> Despite this, however, he did sometimes work with some of the best in the business, as part of a team.<ref name="sote" /><ref name="rr" /> In [[0 BBY/Legends|0 BBY]], [[Skorr/Legends|Skorr]], a prominent bounty hunter in the [[Bright Jewel Cluster/Legends|Bright Jewel Cluster]], subcontracted Furlag to help him execute an Imperial [[Bounty/Legends|bounty]] on an [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] agent named [[Raleigh Dawn|Kestrel]], as well as several other prospective Rebels, on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Ord Mantell/Legends|Ord Mantell]]. Skorr was working for [[Imperial Security Bureau/Legends|Imperial Security Bureau]] operative [[Mar Barezz]], and also hired bounty hunting duo [[4-LOM/Legends|4-LOM]] and [[Zuckuss/Legends|Zuckuss]], who were among the best bounty hunters in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]].<ref name="esb">{{Film|V}}</ref>

[[File:Furlag_angry.jpg|thumb|right|Furlag, furious with Skorr after Kestrel's escape.]]
Skorr had tracked the Rebels to a [[Spaceport/Legends|spaceport]] on the planet, and he, Zuckuss, 4-LOM and Furlag made their way there. En route, Skorr contacted Barezz to appraise him of their progress. As the bounty hunters entered the [[Hangar/Legends|docking bay]] where the Rebels were preparing to leave the planet, Skorr spotted [[Raleigh Dawn|Kestrel]], a young woman who had previously encroached on his territory, among the Rebels. The bounty hunters began firing at Kestrel as she fled to the Rebels' ship, though she was able to get aboard without being hit. Furlag then concentrated his fire at the fleeing ship, but at such a distance his shots were ineffective, and the Rebels were able to escape. Members of the ISB then arrived, telling the bounty hunters to back off, as they were taking control of the situation. Furious, Furlag vented his frustration at Skorr, and left with Zuckuss and 4-LOM.<ref name="rr" />

